<TITLE> China shares jump towards close, end up 3 pct </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SHANGHAI, June 7 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Chinese shares jumped towards the close on Thursday, ending more than 3 percent higher as institutional investors returned to the market to buy bank, coal and construction-related stocks. The Shanghai Composite Index closed at 3,890.803 points, less than a point off its intra-day high. The official Shanghai Securities News quoted unnamed sources as saying the government had no plan to introduce a stock capital gains tax, which had previously been rumoured. This, and a blizzard of positive commentary about stocks in state-owned media, were seen as more evidence that authorities did not want a further sharp drop of the market, after a plunge triggered by last week's hike in the share trading tax. However, many retail investors who had been burned by the tumble continued to sell into strength on Thursday, while shrinking turnover at the market's highs suggested an extended rise in stocks was probably not beginning, traders said
